Trouble shooting :
------------------
Build config resource : contains build information
On the resources tab you can see if #build is failed or success 
if build is failed you can see log files to see what is the reason for build failure. 
other type of resource is deployment:
 like some of the dependencis which are requrired are not there..
Another type of errors some times, build and deployement succesul, but 
pod level errors can happen. 

For advanced trouble shooting a console in the pod is available to run the commands.
(1) How to Debug Your Node.js Application on OpenShift with Chrome DevTools at 
https://developers.redhat.com/blog/2018/05/15/debug-your-node-js-application-on-openshift-with-chrome-devtools/
(2) Remote Debugging of Java Applications on OpenShift at 
https://servicesblog.redhat.com/2019/03/06/remote-debugging-of-java-applications-on-openshift/

REFERENCES:
